Example demonstrating String grimoire methods and functionality.

This script showcases various string manipulation operations available
through the String grimoire including case conversion, length calculation,
and string representation. Each operation demonstrates the object-oriented
approach to string handling in Carrion.
```

# Create a String grimoire instance with initial text
s = String("Hello")

# Display the string representation
print("String:", s.to_string())

# Show the length of the string
print("Length:", s.length())

# Demonstrate case conversion to uppercase
print("Upper:", s.upper())

# Demonstrate case conversion to lowercase
print("Lower:", s.lower())